1
00:00:05,320 --> 00:00:07,080
A hoe? What are you gonna do with that?

2
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:10,320
A phone that keeps disgusting clips deserves this.

3
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,040
Ow, get out.

4
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:15,560
Marry me.

5
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:17,320
I do.

6
00:00:23,040 --> 00:00:24,080
Parrot lady.

7
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,320
I have to go now.

8
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:28,720
Please take care of P’Klao, Pidpee, Muedmon.

9
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:30,600
Jon and Pao too.

10
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,280
You have to love P’Klao a lot, okay?

11
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:34,000
She said she’s leaving.

12
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,480
and asked me to take care of you for her.

13
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:45,800
Auntie, you can leave the flowers right here.

14
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:47,360
- Okay.
- Thank you.

15
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:49,600
Uncle, I was actually about to ask you.

16
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:51,280
Where's Jiw's motorcycle?

17
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,640
Probably at his house.

18
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,240
In that case, could I ask

19
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:56,840
someone to bring it and park it in front of his portrait?

20
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:58,720
It was his favorite thing.

21
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:01,600
Auntie, I wanted to talk to you about

22
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,240
the dinner for the guests tonight.

23
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:25,080
Are you okay?

24
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:26,960
I'm okay.

25
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:29,120
Drink some water first.

26
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,640
Thank you.

27
00:01:35,039 --> 00:01:37,360
For helping take care of everything.

28
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:40,440
Both me and Jiw's relatives

29
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,840
have just been sitting in shock.

30
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:44,000
No one could handle anything.

31
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:46,680
It's really okay.

32
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:49,320
I've already taken care of everything for you.

33
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:51,800
Then,

34
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,400
let's go home and take a shower.

35
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:57,120
Get some rest, then come back out
before the funeral prayers start.

36
00:01:57,240 --> 00:02:00,840
A-And we don't need to help the aunties cook?

37
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,600
No need.

38
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:05,960
I already gave them money to handle everything.

39
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:09,600
The other day, Jiw appeared in his relative's dream.

40
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,360
He said he wanted minced pork rice porridge.

41
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:17,960
Jiw's been appearing in everyone's dreams.

42
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,120
But he's never come to mine.

43
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,600
Because he loves his big sister the most.

44
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:29,560
He probably doesn't want you to worry about him.

45
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:35,880
Jiw.

46
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:40,320
You've found peace now, right?

47
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:47,640
I don't have to worry about you anymore, right?

48
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,200
Before this,

49
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,160
Jiw went around telling everyone

50
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,840
that at his funeral,

51
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:50,760
he didn't want anyone wearing black.

52
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:52,480
Because

53
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,600
he wanted to see everyone happy.

54
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,320
He stayed cheeky until the very end.

55
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:04,840
So then,

56
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,120
don't stay sad for too long.

57
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,600
Live your life happily.

58
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,640
Smile a lot.

59
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,519
Just like Jiw said.

60
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,480
You've been busy taking care of

61
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,880
Jiw's funeral since this morning.

62
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,280
You must be exhausted, right?

63
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:30,040
Thank you for coming to help me.

64
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,320
Without you, I would've fallen apart.

65
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,040
I love you.

66
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,159
Actually, at first,

67
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,080
Jiw told me

68
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,960
to hold the funeral prayers for just one night
and cremate him right away.

69
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,760
So it wouldn't cost too much.

70
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:49,360
But I wanted to keep him for all seven days first.

71
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,960
Because I still couldn't accept it.

72
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,280
I still don't want to admit that

73
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:58,640
Jiw is really gone.

74
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:00,800
But

75
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,960
the last day has finally come.

76
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:10,800
For anything wrong I've ever done,

77
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:14,200
anything that hurt you,

78
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,640
I'm sorry, Jiw.

79
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,960
Please forgive me.

80
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:24,440
And I'll forgive you too.

81
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,600
If there really is a next life,

82
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:31,720
I hope we get to meet again.

83
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,960
I hope you're healthy and strong.

84
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,000
No pain.

85
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,000
No sickness.

86
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:43,120
So you can stay and play with me forever.

87
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,000
You damn tapeworm.

88
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:53,400
Please forgive me and Si too, Jiw.

89
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,000
Who's there?

90
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:35,760
Si.

91
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:38,000
You have visitors.

92
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:40,560
- Ta-da, Si.
- Dad.

93
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,920
Mom, Song.

94
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,560
How did you all get here?

95
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,720
We hadn't seen you for days, so we got worried.

96
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,520
And a few days ago,

97
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:51,440
you came to Bangkok but didn't go home.

98
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,800
Is something wrong? Are you upset with us?

99
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:55,960
No.

100
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,960
I'm fine, and there's no problem at all.

101
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,560
It's just that lately,

102
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,800
I've been busy with Jiw's funeral.

103
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,360
P'Klao's employee.

104
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:06,720
And also,

105
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:10,680
I've been busy planning the housing project too.

106
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,360
Everyone, have a seat first.

107
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,440
I'll be right back.

108
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,520
Okay.

109
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:20,960
Here you go.

110
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,640
Water and crispy rice snacks.

111
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:26,400
- Crispy rice snacks?
- Yep.

112
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,200
Is it anything like a farm truck?

113
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,400
Very similar. Putt putt putt.

114
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,000
- You like that, huh?
- Yep.

115
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,320
- Thank you.
- Wanna try the sound?

116
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,800
- I'm good.
- Alright.

117
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:37,640
By the way, you look familiar.

118
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:41,560
Like some singer... F something.

119
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,480
- Don't you think?
- Oh, maybe a little.

120
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:47,760
Oh, but that person is handsome though.

121
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,760
Are you saying you're that handsome too?

122
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,680
Why did you bring me this check?

123
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,720
And it's for a hundred million.

124
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:03,720
It's the bride price, Dad.

125
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,800
But this is your signature.

126
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:10,040
Did Klao borrow money from you?

127
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:13,000
No, she didn't borrow money from me.

128
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,880
I just wanted

129
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:17,640
to pay the wedding bride price myself.

130
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,800
Wait a second, Si.

131
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:24,360
So you and Klao

132
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,960
are really getting married?

133
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,080
Yes, Mom.

134
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,080
P'Klao and I,

135
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,960
we're really getting married.

136
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,640
But why do you have to pay
the bride price yourself?

137
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,200
Are you scared you won't get married?

138
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,680
No, Dad.

139
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,800
I just don't want

140
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:43,200
P'Klao to carry too much burden.

141
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:46,200
Just lowering the land rent for us

142
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,240
is already a huge amount.

143
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:50,920
So I decided to pay the bride price myself.

144
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:55,240
But would Klao really agree to that?

145
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:59,240
She doesn't seem like that kind of person, P'Si.

146
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:02,320
I'll try talking to her again later.

147
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,360
She's been really busy lately.

148
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:08,360
But Mom and Dad, please take it first.

149
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:11,880
I think if Klao finds out about this,

150
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,640
she definitely won't agree.

151
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:15,560
She doesn't know about this, right?

152
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:19,720
I'll try talking to her again, Mom.

153
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,080
I only ask for one thing.

154
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,960
Just one thing.

155
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:28,600
Mom and Dad,

156
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:31,440
please don't ask her
for an expensive bride price.

157
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,600
Oh, sweetheart.

158
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:38,040
Why are you thinking such silly things, huh?

159
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:39,640
By the way,

160
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,240
you're doing a housing project?

161
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:45,760
Song told me about it already, but not in detail.

162
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,960
You're investing in this business?

163
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:51,520
Yes. It's still in the beginning stages right now.

164
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,400
It'll probably take a long time to finish.

165
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,760
Once I finally succeed,

166
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,400
I'll take everyone to see it.

167
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,360
And I want Mom and Dad

168
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,440
to be the ones opening the project too.

169
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:05,280
- Wow, that serious, huh?
- Wow.

170
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,000
How about this then?

171
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:11,160
Keep this money to invest in your business.

172
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:13,520
As for the bride price,

173
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:15,240
you don't need to worry because

174
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,040
we also

175
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,120
don't want anything from Klao.

176
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,800
As long as she loves and takes care of you,

177
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,440
that's enough for us.

178
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,760
Okay?

179
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:32,560
Thank you, Mom and Dad.

180
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,000
Oh, and,

181
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:37,200
where did Klao go?

182
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,600
There she is.

183
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,280
She came at the perfect time, Mom.

184
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:43,080
There she is.

185
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:49,800
Someone told me your parents
and Song came by the house.

186
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:51,440
Is something wrong?

187
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:55,600
Well, my daughter is getting married,

188
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:57,480
so I wanted to see with my own eyes

189
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,560
whether she's living comfortably

190
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:02,920
or if she got tricked into a hard life.

191
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:06,160
You scared me.

192
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:09,240
I thought something serious had happened.

193
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:14,560
P'Klao didn't kidnap me here.

194
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,960
I came to live with her willingly.

195
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:20,000
- Wow.
- So then,

196
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,280
Dad, Mom, and Song,

197
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,840
are you really sure

198
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:27,160
you want to know what living
with P'Klao is really like?

199
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:28,800
Mm-hm.

200
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:36,840
Ready?

201
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,760
Okay.

202
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,560
Honey.

203
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,360
- What do you think, Dad?
- Wow.

204
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:51,800
This is it.

205
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:53,680
This is where I live with P'Klao.

206
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,840
It's beautiful.

207
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,520
Right now we're waiting for the rice to flower.

208
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:04,360
- It's already flowering.
- Yeah.

209
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:08,960
Wow.

210
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:15,200
- Wow.
- What do you think?

211
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:17,400
All this land here

212
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,280
belongs to P'Klao's family.

213
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,840
It's all used for farming.

214
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:21,840
Huh?

215
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:25,040
All this land belongs to Klao?

216
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:27,240
Yes. It's just that

217
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:29,760
my parents liked collecting land.

218
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,600
After they passed away,

219
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,600
none of the children dared to sell it.

220
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:36,040
So we kept the land for farming and

221
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:38,760
hired local people so they'd have jobs.

222
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:41,360
And that's not even including
the land in town

223
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,720
that P'Klao rents out.

224
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:46,240
Plus the land in Bangkok
that our family rents for a shopping mall.

225
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:49,960
Wow, Klao really is a true countryside millionaire.

226
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:52,320
When harvest season gets close,

227
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:54,800
she lets the local villagers
come help harvest the rice

228
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,520
instead of using harvest machines.

229
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:58,520
That way the local villagers have work

230
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:00,520
and can earn an income too.

231
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,960
And the Suphan Hom Mali 918 rice

232
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,400
is one of the products from here.

233
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,920
The villagers all work together to produce it.

234
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:10,680
Actually, we should thank Si

235
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,079
for coming up with the idea.

236
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:14,079
Wow.

237
00:17:14,359 --> 00:17:15,680
Is this your first time

238
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:19,560
- actually being useful?
- Oh please.

239
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:22,119
Come on.

240
00:17:22,359 --> 00:17:24,240
Dad, Mom, Song,

241
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:27,520
I'm gonna introduce you to my best friends.

242
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,040
- Hm?
- Best friends?

243
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,760
- Yep.
- Here?

244
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,040
My best friends.

245
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,600
Alright, okay. Let's go.

246
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:36,040
- Go.
- Let's go.

247
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,920
These two are named Pidpee and Muedmon.

248
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:43,680
Oh my.

249
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,480
What do you mean, "oh my"?

250
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:48,280
She's this gorgeous.

251
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:50,440
And she's pretty too. Oh my gosh.

252
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:52,200
She's beautiful too.

253
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,680
- You startled me.
- Don't mess with them.

254
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,400
- Don't touch them.
- But I want to pet them too.

255
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:57,720
If you're gonna compliment her,
you have to say

256
00:17:57,720 --> 00:18:01,600
pretty pretty because Pidpee is female.
She's the mom.

257
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:04,120
As for Muedmon, he's the son. Male.

258
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:06,680
- Oh, I see.
- If I hadn't come to see this with my own eyes,

259
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:09,840
I would've never believed
you've changed this much.

260
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:13,760
P'Si, can I try riding the buffalo?

261
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,600
Ta-da. And this

262
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:32,320
is Sam Chuk, the historic market of Suphan Buri.

263
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:35,000
A hundred-year-old market by the Tha Chin River.

264
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,400
There are so many delicious things here.

265
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:40,400
It's only a two-hour drive from Bangkok.

266
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:45,760
Oh.

267
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,280
(Sam Chuk Hundred-Year Market)

268
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:48,920
Hey, wait for me.

269
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,240
Si.

270
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,320
- What's this?
- You didn't wait for me.

271
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:57,720
- Miang kham.
- Can I have one?

272
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:21,440
They said if you come to Suphan Buri,

273
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,640
you have to buy this to take home.

274
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,960
- We'll take two.
- Ah, okay.

275
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,400
Mm. Shopping for everything.

276
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,400
Come on, I'll pay for it myself.

277
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:33,440
At first I was going to take
everyone to a restaurant,

278
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:36,760
but after thinking about it,
I'd rather show off my cooking skills.

279
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:39,400
Because Si has her regular vendors

280
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:42,080
who pick only the best ingredients
and freshest produce

281
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:43,760
and deliver them right to us.

282
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,360
Wow, you've lived here long enough
to know all the vendors already?

283
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,440
Yep.

284
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,600
Her name is Auntie Phuang.

285
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:52,760
She owns one of those mobile grocery trucks.

286
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:53,920
She buys things from the market

287
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:56,760
and sells them to the villagers
and people around here.

288
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,200
Whenever I want something,

289
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:00,440
I just tell her
and she'll deliver it right to me.

290
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,720
Oh.

291
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:04,400
Why don't you take Mom
and Dad to freshen up first?

292
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:05,800
Then just sit back and relax.

293
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:09,000
I'll show off my skills for dinner tonight.

294
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,200
Yes, honey.

295
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:16,360
I've never seen you like this before.

296
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,520
It's true, Mom.

297
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:21,600
P'Si looks relaxed, cheerful, and happy

298
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:24,000
in a way we've really never seen before.

299
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:27,040
She's not the same irritable P'Si anymore.

300
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:32,000
I can't believe it myself either.

301
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,240
That I've changed this much.

302
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:35,920
Now that I've seen it with my own eyes,

303
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:37,160
I feel relieved.

304
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,520
And now I believe

305
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:40,040
that Klao really can

306
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:42,840
make my daughter truly happy.

307
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,400
Dad.

308
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:47,960
Mom.

309
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:50,520
I'm sorry.

310
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,000
For all this time,

311
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,920
I haven't been a very lovable daughter.

312
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:57,760
But

313
00:20:58,120 --> 00:20:59,720
from now on,

314
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,600
I promise

315
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:05,640
that I'll become the lovable daughter Mom
and Dad deserve.

316
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,040
You too, Song.

317
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,640
I'm sorry

318
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,560
for always thinking badly of you.

319
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,240
And

320
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:25,840
for snapping at you all the time.

321
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:28,960
But now I know there's no one

322
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:31,160
who loves me

323
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:33,400
and wishes me well more than

324
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:34,720
Mom, Dad, and you.

325
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,520
But there's one more person

326
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:48,760
who loooves you very much.

327
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,160
Over there. That person.

328
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:00,120
P'Si,

329
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:02,720
I've never been mad at you.

330
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:04,760
Because no matter what,

331
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,920
you're still my only big sister.

332
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:12,640
Thank you, Song.

333
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:14,760
For never being angry at me.

334
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:19,760
Come here, you two little troublemakers.

335
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:30,960
Actually, you all should stay the night here.

336
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,720
Tomorrow morning I want
to take everyone to pray at the temple.

337
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,920
The monk there is really sacred.

338
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:38,600
My daughter already gets to
marry someone wonderful like you.

339
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:40,680
I don't think we need to ask for
any blessings anymore.

340
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,920
Maybe next time, Klao.

341
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:46,000
We didn't prepare to stay overnight today.

342
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:48,560
And we don't want to trouble you either.

343
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:50,480
We'll get going then.

344
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,240
Wait.

345
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:56,480
My parents

346
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:58,400
passed away many years ago.

347
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:00,680
Would you two mind if

348
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:04,560
I asked to become another daughter of yours?

349
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:09,920
Of course, dear.

350
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:12,600
Come be our daughter.

351
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:20,240
Then can I be another little sister to P'Klao too?

352
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,120
Of course.

353
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:29,920
Um.

354
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,240
Mom, Dad,

355
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:36,040
would you mind if

356
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:40,560
I wanted to hold my wedding with P'Klao here?

357
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:43,640
I don't want to have it in Bangkok.

358
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:01,640
How do I look?

359
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:04,400
Am I pretty enough to be a bride yet?

360
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,640
You’re beautiful.

361
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:14,440
My big sister is the prettiest.

362
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:17,240
I’m nervous.

363
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:28,200
What’s wrong?

364
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,920
Why are you crying?

365
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:33,400
I’m just so happy.

366
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:36,440
My big sister I’ve been
with since we were kids.

367
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:38,640
She’s finally becoming a bride.

368
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:42,120
My good girl.

369
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:44,680
You’re not supposed to cry on
a happy day like this.

370
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:47,440
You spent so long getting all pretty.

371
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:49,120
Your makeup’s gonna get ruined.

372
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,720
I’m just happy.

373
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:03,120
Si, are you done yet?

374
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:05,120
The groom’s procession is almost here.

375
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:06,880
I’m ready, Mom.

376
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:15,000
How do I look? Am I pretty, Dad?

377
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,240
Mom.

378
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:22,040
Mom, Dad.

379
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:26,040
You’re all crying along with Song now.

380
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,480
Why?

381
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:30,400
I’m happy that my beautiful daughter here.

382
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:31,840
finally found someone to marry her.

383
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,680
Daddy’s little angel.

384
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,680
is really getting married now?

385
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:40,560
Honey.

386
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,680
Thinking about it now makes me emotional.

387
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,040
We raised her since she was little.

388
00:25:47,040 --> 00:25:48,880
And now you’re getting married, sweetheart.

389
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:54,520
Come to think of it, we’re getting old too.

390
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,560
I’m not old yet.

391
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:05,920
Come on, Mom, Dad, Si.

392
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,840
Let’s take a photo together.

393
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:08,840
Come here.

394
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,200
Smile.

395
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:32,600
- Here they come.
- Here they come.

396
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,400
- Here they come.
- Here they come.

397
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:35,640
There they are.

398
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,240
Look at that smug face.

399
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,920
So smug.

400
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,360
Keep them moving.

401
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,920
Keep them moving.

402
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:52,560
Come on, everyone.

403
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:55,320
Take it easy now.

404
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:59,240
Today is a beautiful and auspicious day.

405
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:02,320
Klao’s family, the groom’s side.

406
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:04,440
has brought the wedding procession.

407
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:08,080
bringing prosperity and good fortune.

408
00:27:08,120 --> 00:27:10,680
to the bride’s family today.

409
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:14,600
Si, may we have permission to come inside?

410
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:17,280
Wow, with a procession this grand.

411
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,760
I wanna hear it louder one more time.

412
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:20,960
Come on, everyone, one more time.

413
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,680
Woo.

414
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:26,120
Happy now? Here you go.

415
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:28,080
- Here, take it.
- This one's for you.

416
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:29,120
Can we go in now?

417
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,640
Ooh, this envelope’s heavy.

418
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:33,320
- You may enter now.
- Alright.

419
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:36,920
- Please come in.
- Come on in.

420
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:38,920
Come on in.

421
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:42,040
Here they come, tra-la-la.

422
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:45,120
Keep them moving.

423
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:46,720
- Keep them moving.
- Keep them moving.

424
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:48,400
We got a goat.

425
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:50,040
We got a goat.

426
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,600
Cook it with rice.

427
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:52,920
Cook it with rice.

428
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:54,840
Daddy’s not home.

429
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,520
Tra-la-la.

430
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:08,680
- Here they come.
- Here they come.

431
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:10,720
- Here they come.
- Here they come.

432
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:12,040
There’s more.

433
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,720
Still not done yet.

434
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:16,120
- Not running out anytime soon.
- I’m running out of cash though.

435
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:18,080
- Here, I’m giving it all away.
- Thank you.

436
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:20,920
- I’ve got nothing left now.
- Just let it go.

437
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,720
Cook it with rice.

438
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:24,320
Cook it with rice.

439
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:25,920
Daddy’s not home.

440
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:27,840
Tra-la-la.

441
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,240
Today.

442
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:52,400
I’m not just here to take you.

443
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:54,360
as my bride.

444
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:57,720
But.

445
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:01,480
I’m here to take you as my life partner.

446
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:07,720
Are you ready to be my life partner?

447
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:12,000
I’m ready.

448
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:15,320
to be your life partner forever.

449
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:03,240
I’ve got a wife now.

450
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:15,000
(Klao &amp; Si 15.05.2026.)

451
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:43,400
If you love each other deeply,
be patient with each other too.

452
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:46,400
Don’t be too stubborn with Klao, alright?

453
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:42,880
From now on.

454
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:46,760
I wish Klao and my beloved Si.

455
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:48,880
a long and happy life together.

456
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,880
No matter what happens.

457
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:52,840
I hope you forgive each other.

458
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:54,880
Share both joy and hardship together.

459
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:57,120
Never leave each other behind.

460
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:01,200
And I hope this home of yours.

461
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:03,120
will always be filled with happiness.

462
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:04,680
forever.

463
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:07,360
This bed.

464
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:09,200
belongs to the two of you.

465
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,480
Don’t let anyone come between you.

466
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:17,520
And if Si gets stubborn.

467
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:19,560
you can handle her, I allow it.

468
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:24,560
What are you whispering about?

469
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:26,600
I can hear you, you know.

470
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:28,480
Go on now, go.

471
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:29,600
Here, let me help.

472
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:51,440
Who would’ve thought a country girl like me.

473
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:53,880
would end up with a hi-so wife like you?

474
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:56,680
When you say the word wife.

475
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:58,600
it gives me butterflies somehow.

476
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:00,480
Why’s that?

477
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:04,040
Because I’m shy.

478
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:08,240
Si.

479
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:11,440
is Klao’s wife now.

480
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,480
Hello.

481
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:52,200
Who are you here to see?

482
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,000
Is Si here?

483
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:56,120
Si? Oh.

484
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:58,360
Si’s in the bridal chamber ceremony right now.

485
00:33:58,400 --> 00:34:00,120
They’re all lovey-dovey in there.

486
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,800
Oh, are you Si’s friend?

487
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:03,120
Did you come to congratulate her?

488
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:05,560
- Come on in, hurry.
- No.

489
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:06,600
Huh?

490
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:08,639
I’m not going in, I’ll wait here.

491
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:10,719
Just tell her Jane is here to see her.

492
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,320
Jane is here.

493
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:14,560
Which Jane? Jane? Which Jane?

494
00:34:14,560 --> 00:34:16,080
Just tell her Jane, that’s enough.

495
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:18,000
She’ll know, stop asking so many questions.

496
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:19,280
Go get her for me.

497
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,320
Well.

498
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:23,440
I’m asking nicely, so answer nicely too.

499
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:24,800
So which Jane?

500
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:27,280
Jane Yannathip?
You here for a fortune reading?

501
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:28,600
Jane, Si’s ex.

502
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:32,199
- Oh, Jane the ex. I was wondering who.
- Uh, go get her already.

503
00:34:32,639 --> 00:34:34,239
Si’s ex, Jane.

504
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:37,840
So it’s you. What are you doing here?

505
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:40,960
Can you speak nicely?
Do we even know each other?

506
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,480
You may not know me.

507
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:45,320
but I know you very well.

508
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:46,960
Jane, the one Jon pooped on.

509
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:48,280
Ah, that’s you, right?

510
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:50,400
You’re the bitch Jon pooped
on the other day, right?

511
00:34:50,440 --> 00:34:52,880
Good grief, everyone in
Suphan Buri knows you now.

512
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:55,239
Wherever you came from,
go right back there.

513
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:56,880
There’s a wedding celebration here.

514
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:58,760
Bad luck like you doesn’t belong here.

515
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:00,080
- Oh, that’s how you wanna talk?
- Uh.

516
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:01,800
Great. I’m about to slap you flat.

517
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:04,600
Come on then, where are you?

518
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:13,760
- Jane.
- I told you to go get her.

519
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:21,880
Klao.

520
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:26,400
Klao.

521
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:29,080
Come here.

522
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:33,280
Who did you go fight with?

523
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,240
Why do you look such a mess?

524
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:36,640
I’ll tell you in a second.

525
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:39,360
But where’s Si? Where is she?

526
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:40,680
She’s lying down in the room.

527
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:44,520
- So here’s what happened.
- Hey.

528
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:45,800
I haven’t told you yet.

529
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:48,400
Oh my god, you two are ridiculous.

530
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:07,640
Hurry up.

531
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,240
Open the door for me.

532
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:11,520
Keep an eye out for me, okay?

533
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:13,360
- In case anyone walks by.
- Open this door right now, I’m coming out.

534
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,560
Sure thing.

535
00:36:14,600 --> 00:36:17,200
- Uh, can I ask you for one favor?
- Sure.

536
00:36:17,280 --> 00:36:19,000
Give her hell for me.

537
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:21,280
She slapped me, she pulled my hair.

538
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,120
my diamond even fell off.

539
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,280
Say no more.

540
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:25,880
- You ready?
- Ready.

541
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:28,480
You pig, just wait till I get out there.

542
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,360
Let me out. Let me out.

543
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:33,440
This is my house.

544
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,600
What right do you have to
order me around?

545
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:35,600
Just wait till I get out there.

546
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:37,360
I’m calling the police on all of you.

547
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:38,880
And what exactly are you reporting?

548
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:40,680
A whole bunch of charges.

549
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:43,320
You assaulted me and
unlawfully detained me.

550
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:44,720
And if I think harder, there’ll be more.

551
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:45,920
You dare?

552
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:48,280
Why wouldn’t I dare?

553
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:50,080
What did I tell you before?

554
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:52,280
I told you to stay away from Si.

555
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:56,640
It’s not like I wanted to come mess with you anyway.

556
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:58,880
But I brought this for you.

557
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:01,720
The letter.

558
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:04,760
you sent through your lawyer
threatening me to stay away from you two.

559
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:15,280
You already signed it, so leave.

560
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:21,480
Oh? And how are you
gonna pay me those ten million?

561
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:24,200
Oh, about the contract.

562
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:26,480
my brother had the lawyer handle it.

563
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:29,040
You can wait to receive
the money from the lawyer then.

564
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:33,640
You think you can scam me, bitch?

565
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,160
Let go.

566
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:42,840
This is what you get for ruining my wedding.

567
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:46,200
You country bumpkin,
just wait, you’re going to jail.

568
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:47,760
I’m not letting you off easy.

569
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:51,720
Did Klao go in there to deal with Jane or.

570
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:53,640
did Jane go in there to deal with Klao?

571
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:02,560
Klao, are you done yet?

572
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,240
There has to be a secret code.

573
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:08,160
What if Jane tricks us again?

574
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:11,360
Give us the secret code. Kiss Jon for us.

575
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:14,400
Cluck cluck cluck.

576
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:16,760
That’s right, the real deal. Come here.

577
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:43,800
Thank you so much.

578
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:45,360
Come take a photo with us.

579
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:57,920
Go ahead, sweetheart.

580
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:10,320
I don’t really have much to say.

581
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:13,320
other than thank you
to all the uncles and aunties.

582
00:39:13,360 --> 00:39:15,240
and everyone here.

583
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:18,400
for honoring us by coming to our wedding.

584
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:22,120
Please eat well and have lots of fun.

585
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:30,960
As for me, there’s not much either.
I just want to.

586
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:34,600
thank all the brothers
and sisters of the 918 community.

587
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:37,040
for loving and caring for me.

588
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:38,960
From now on.

589
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:42,720
please accept me as a real
daughter-in-law of this community.

590
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:46,360
If there’s anything, please feel free
to teach and guide me.

591
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:48,840
Sure.

592
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:52,800
Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.

593
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:55,840
Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.

594
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:58,000
- Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.
- No, stop, I’m embarrassed.

595
00:39:58,040 --> 00:39:59,640
- Everyone’s cheering for us.
- Kiss. Kiss.

596
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:02,160
- Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.
- It’d be awkward if we don’t.

597
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:04,600
Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.

598
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,640
Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.

599
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:15,560
This wedding’s finally over for me.

600
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,840
I’m sorry. Where are you taking me?

601
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:21,760
You really never stop talking.
The whole point of me doing this.

602
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:24,120
- is so you’ll stop talking.
- Well.

603
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:26,720
you still haven’t told me where you’re taking me.

604
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:30,360
- Why are you asking me questions right now?
- Where are you sending me? Take the rope off.

605
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:32,200
You sure love talking. Here, speak then.

606
00:40:32,240 --> 00:40:36,200
- So, what’s your story anyway?
- Take the rope off.

607
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:38,040
- Take the rope off.
- Sit still.

608
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:41,960
Alright, get out now. This
is as far as I’m taking you.

609
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:43,080
How can you just drop me off here?

610
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:45,800
Take me all the way there.
How am I supposed to get there? How do I go?

611
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:48,320
Hey, gas costs money.
I’m not your ride service.

612
00:40:48,360 --> 00:40:50,120
I’m not taking you all the way. Get out.

613
00:40:50,160 --> 00:40:52,480
No. You have to take me there.

614
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:53,760
I said get out.

615
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:54,920
I’m not getting out.

616
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:56,720
Wow, you’re really asking for it.

617
00:40:56,760 --> 00:40:58,040
What are you doing?

618
00:40:58,040 --> 00:41:00,160
Get out already. Go.

619
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,520
- Hey.
- Wait, take your stuff too.

620
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:05,040
- Here, take your stuff too.
- What?

621
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:08,360
- Don’t leave it in my car.
- Don’t, don’t go.

622
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,760
I have money, I’ll transfer it to you.
Please take me there.

623
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:12,560
How much are you paying, Auntie Phuang?

624
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:14,760
You.

625
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:18,120
Then how am I supposed to get home?

626
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:26,600
P’Klao.

627
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:32,240
The water’s not running again tonight.

628
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:34,920
Looks like we’ll have to bathe outside again.

629
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:37,680
Honey.

630
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:40,360
Are you okay?

631
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:46,240
You miss Jiw, huh?

632
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:48,560
If she were here.

633
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:51,360
our wedding would’ve been even more fun.

634
00:41:52,720 --> 00:41:53,960
I think.

635
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:56,240
we’d have a headache instead.

636
00:41:56,600 --> 00:41:57,800
If Jiw were here.

637
00:41:57,840 --> 00:42:01,120
she’d probably make everyone
at the wedding dance nonstop.

638
00:42:05,920 --> 00:42:06,920
But.

639
00:42:07,680 --> 00:42:09,440
now that you mention it.

640
00:42:10,400 --> 00:42:12,520
I really miss her too.

641
00:42:24,520 --> 00:42:26,760
The melon farm girl.

642
00:42:26,800 --> 00:42:28,720
of Suphan City.

643
00:42:28,760 --> 00:42:31,480
Her name is famous everywhere.

644
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:33,480
Talked about all across.

645
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:35,920
the whole town.

646
00:42:36,560 --> 00:42:38,680
You used to complain about me.

647
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:40,600
always listening to this song.

648
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:42,680
And now you suddenly like it?

649
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:45,320
Well, you kept playing it for me.

650
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,400
every single day.

651
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:49,880
Even if I didn’t like it, I had to eventually.

652
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:52,360
Come here, let me.

653
00:42:52,360 --> 00:42:53,840
wash your hair for you too.

654
00:42:54,080 --> 00:42:55,080
Come on.

655
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:28,000
The weather’s so nice today.

656
00:43:29,600 --> 00:43:31,120
Or maybe.

657
00:43:32,240 --> 00:43:34,080
we should sleep out here tonight.

658
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:37,680
Oh wow, if we sleep out here.

659
00:43:37,720 --> 00:43:40,040
we’ll probably get bitten by mosquitoes all over.

660
00:43:40,120 --> 00:43:42,280
Or catch a cold because.

661
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:44,280
we’d be covered in dew all night.

662
00:43:50,040 --> 00:43:51,840
Honey.

663
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:55,360
What’s married life like?

664
00:43:57,600 --> 00:43:59,920
I honestly have no idea.

665
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:01,600
how I’m supposed to act.

666
00:44:04,640 --> 00:44:06,040
I think.

667
00:44:06,760 --> 00:44:08,480
actually.

668
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:10,440
a wedding.

669
00:44:10,640 --> 00:44:13,240
is just the beginning of married life.

670
00:44:14,840 --> 00:44:16,480
What comes after this.

671
00:44:16,840 --> 00:44:18,600
is the real life.

672
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:21,600
From now on.

673
00:44:22,800 --> 00:44:24,560
if anything happens between us.

674
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:26,960
we have to talk to each other.

675
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:30,240
and slowly learn to understand each other.

676
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:56,040
Honey, who was that woman?

677
00:44:57,200 --> 00:45:00,320
Si, calm down first.

678
00:45:01,840 --> 00:45:03,360
How am I supposed to stay calm?

679
00:45:03,360 --> 00:45:06,320
I only went to Bangkok for a few days
to oversee construction.

680
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:08,360
and there’s already a woman
coming to see you at home?

681
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:13,800
Her name is Tuktah.

682
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:15,600
Her name is Tuktah.

683
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:18,160
I’ve known her since she was little.

684
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:20,600
She’s Aunt Tan’s daughter from the house.

685
00:45:20,640 --> 00:45:22,280
over there.

686
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:25,080
She just graduated recently.

687
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:27,000
and she probably went to
visit relatives in Surat Thani.

688
00:45:27,040 --> 00:45:29,160
So she bought me some salted eggs as a gift.

689
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:30,200
That’s all.

690
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:32,160
And she doesn’t know you’re married?

691
00:45:32,240 --> 00:45:33,640
She does. Look.

692
00:45:33,680 --> 00:45:36,000
She just brought me something.

693
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:38,840
and you kicked it away like that. Such a waste.

694
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:42,120
A waste? Why, I’m not allowed to kick it away?

695
00:45:42,120 --> 00:45:43,520
Was it really that bad?

696
00:45:44,240 --> 00:45:46,160
I didn’t say you were bad.

697
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:49,000
Because I look at you with love.

698
00:45:49,440 --> 00:45:52,040
No matter how badly you behave.

699
00:45:52,080 --> 00:45:54,240
I’ll still love you the same.

700
00:45:55,040 --> 00:45:57,720
But other people don’t look at you.

701
00:45:57,720 --> 00:45:59,200
the way I do.

702
00:45:59,200 --> 00:46:01,440
I don’t want other people thinking badly of you.

703
00:46:02,920 --> 00:46:05,360
I don’t care how other people see me.

704
00:46:05,360 --> 00:46:06,760
But I do.

705
00:46:07,040 --> 00:46:10,720
I don’t want people thinking you’re not lovable.

706
00:46:10,720 --> 00:46:11,720
Because.

707
00:46:12,160 --> 00:46:14,640
I love you and care about you.

708
00:46:14,920 --> 00:46:15,920
Alright.

709
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:19,640
If what I did wasn’t lovable.

710
00:46:19,880 --> 00:46:22,320
then I’ll work on myself, okay?

711
00:46:22,400 --> 00:46:26,040
But you’re not allowed to get close
to other women anymore.

712
00:46:26,120 --> 00:46:27,920
You’re married to me now.

713
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:30,280
I have the right to be possessive and jealous.

714
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:31,360
Do you understand?

715
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:33,240
I understand. Here.

716
00:46:43,240 --> 00:46:45,440
The salted eggs are all smashed now.

717
00:46:48,240 --> 00:46:49,440
Si.

718
00:46:50,800 --> 00:46:52,560
Close the wardrobe gently.

719
00:46:52,600 --> 00:46:54,240
There are pajamas inside.

720
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:57,320
Don’t make lame jokes right now.

721
00:46:57,320 --> 00:46:58,840
I’m not laughing.

722
00:47:00,840 --> 00:47:02,320
Wait a second.

723
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:05,040
You’ve been away for days.

724
00:47:05,120 --> 00:47:07,840
Let me kiss you so I stop missing you.

725
00:47:08,320 --> 00:47:11,320
Don’t come acting all sweet like this.

726
00:47:11,880 --> 00:47:13,280
People who do something wrong.

727
00:47:13,600 --> 00:47:16,120
always try to cover it up by being extra nice.

728
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:20,400
Are you still mad at me?

729
00:47:20,440 --> 00:47:23,320
I thought we already talked it through earlier.

730
00:47:23,960 --> 00:47:26,480
I understand, but I don’t want to accept it.

731
00:47:28,000 --> 00:47:30,240
Think about it carefully.

732
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:32,960
I’ve always acted like my normal self.

733
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:35,200
We have to meet people.

734
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:36,840
And when we live here.

735
00:47:36,840 --> 00:47:39,080
we have to help each other out.

736
00:47:39,120 --> 00:47:40,920
support one another.

737
00:47:41,040 --> 00:47:42,400
Think about it.

738
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:43,960
When you lived in Bangkok.

739
00:47:43,960 --> 00:47:47,880
did you even know
the name of the person next door?

740
00:47:47,920 --> 00:47:49,000
But here.

741
00:47:49,040 --> 00:47:51,560
we practically know the whole district.

742
00:47:52,800 --> 00:47:54,120
So that’s why.

743
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:56,200
you’ve got women flocking around you.

744
00:47:58,120 --> 00:47:59,920
If you don’t like it.

745
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:03,200
then I’ll try not to get close to any women at all.

746
00:48:03,200 --> 00:48:04,600
Okay?

747
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:20,960
What are you doing? It’s broad daylight.

748
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:22,880
So what if it’s daytime?

749
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:24,920
I missed you.

750
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:01,600
Pew pew.

751
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:05,040
I shot the tire. Flat tire for sure. Pew.

752
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:07,520
- Tuktah.
- Yes?

753
00:49:07,680 --> 00:49:08,680
How did you get here?

754
00:49:08,720 --> 00:49:11,560
Well, I moved back home and have nothing to do.

755
00:49:11,600 --> 00:49:14,360
But I definitely can’t farm like you do.

756
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:17,800
The sun’s too hot. My skin will get ruined.

757
00:49:17,840 --> 00:49:20,680
So I thought I’d try growing vegetables instead.

758
00:49:20,680 --> 00:49:23,640
If you’re free sometime, could you teach me?

759
00:49:24,200 --> 00:49:27,120
Uh, when I’m free, I’ll come teach you.

760
00:49:28,720 --> 00:49:31,080
Oh no, the car won’t start?

761
00:49:33,000 --> 00:49:35,560
The seat’s so soft.

762
00:49:36,600 --> 00:49:39,200
Uh, I wanted to know, when growing vegetables.

763
00:49:39,200 --> 00:49:41,200
how many times a day do you water them?

764
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:44,240
- Morning and evening is enough.
- Huh?

765
00:49:44,280 --> 00:49:45,720
Really?

766
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:48,760
The car still won’t start?

767
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:51,080
Let me help you.

768
00:49:52,080 --> 00:49:53,360
P’Klao.

769
00:49:53,360 --> 00:49:56,760
My mom said you raise buffaloes too?

770
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:57,960
What are their names again?

771
00:49:58,000 --> 00:49:59,480
I totally forgot.

772
00:49:59,520 --> 00:50:02,040
- They had such cute names.
- Oh.

773
00:50:02,080 --> 00:50:05,280
- The mother is named Pidpee.
- Pidpee.

774
00:50:05,280 --> 00:50:08,440
- Her son is named Muedmon.
- Muedmon.

775
00:50:08,480 --> 00:50:10,080
Oh.

776
00:50:10,080 --> 00:50:12,280
- I should get going now.
- Oh, uh.

777
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:15,880
Oh no, the car still won’t start?

778
00:50:15,920 --> 00:50:17,760
Then let me help you.

779
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:18,800
Together now.

780
00:50:18,840 --> 00:50:21,480
One, two, push.

781
00:50:23,080 --> 00:50:24,160
Still won’t start?

782
00:50:24,200 --> 00:50:25,720
Then let’s try again.

783
00:50:25,760 --> 00:50:28,680
One, two, push.

784
00:50:28,720 --> 00:50:30,280
Did it work?

785
00:50:30,480 --> 00:50:32,440
You need to get out first.

786
00:50:32,480 --> 00:50:35,520
- Otherwise the car won’t start at all.
- Oh, should I help?

787
00:50:35,560 --> 00:50:37,600
Just helping by getting out is enough.

788
00:50:40,760 --> 00:50:42,280
Get out first.

789
00:50:42,320 --> 00:50:45,400
- I really can’t start the car.
- Okay, P’Klao.

790
00:50:49,080 --> 00:50:50,120
I’m leaving now.

791
00:50:50,160 --> 00:50:51,160
Okay.

792
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:55,000
Bye-bye.

793
00:50:59,440 --> 00:51:01,280
Pew pew.

794
00:51:25,880 --> 00:51:26,880
Honey.

795
00:51:27,880 --> 00:51:29,200
You’re back already?

796
00:51:29,440 --> 00:51:32,280
- I missed you so much.
- Oh, honey.

797
00:51:32,400 --> 00:51:36,280
- I smell, I’m all sweaty.
- Let me kiss you. You don’t smell at all.

798
00:51:37,360 --> 00:51:38,680
You smell just fine.

799
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:41,560
Uh, honey.

800
00:51:42,960 --> 00:51:44,200
I need to tell you something.

801
00:51:45,280 --> 00:51:46,360
What is it?

802
00:51:48,400 --> 00:51:50,680
It’s about Tuktah.

803
00:51:54,760 --> 00:51:56,400
That woman again?

804
00:51:57,440 --> 00:51:58,800
Well.

805
00:51:59,160 --> 00:52:02,080
she moved back home already.

806
00:52:02,120 --> 00:52:03,360
I think.

807
00:52:03,360 --> 00:52:06,920
we’re bound to run into each other sometimes.

808
00:52:06,960 --> 00:52:09,680
If you want me to completely avoid talking to her.

809
00:52:09,960 --> 00:52:11,480
I think that’d be hard.

810
00:52:12,040 --> 00:52:14,320
Then why does she have to talk to only you? Huh?

811
00:52:14,360 --> 00:52:15,720
I seriously don’t get it.

812
00:52:16,880 --> 00:52:19,560
I already told you.

813
00:52:19,600 --> 00:52:22,640
I’ve known her since we were kids.

814
00:52:22,760 --> 00:52:25,240
She’s like a little sister to me.

815
00:52:25,680 --> 00:52:29,680
I think we’ll still have to see each other normally.

816
00:52:29,680 --> 00:52:31,600
But there’s really nothing going on.

817
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:33,440
I’m only telling you beforehand because.

818
00:52:33,480 --> 00:52:36,000
I don’t want you finding out later.

819
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:38,880
Then avoid her.

820
00:52:38,960 --> 00:52:40,720
Why do you have to keep talking to her?

821
00:52:41,160 --> 00:52:42,280
Or better yet.

822
00:52:42,320 --> 00:52:44,560
just don’t talk to her or see her at all.

823
00:52:45,040 --> 00:52:46,240
Once you stop bothering with her.

824
00:52:46,280 --> 00:52:47,840
she’ll stop bothering with you too.

825
00:52:54,560 --> 00:52:56,320
If it’s really that hard.

826
00:52:57,000 --> 00:52:58,840
then I’ll handle it myself.

827
00:53:10,920 --> 00:53:12,080
Si.

828
00:53:30,160 --> 00:53:31,280
Si.

829
00:53:31,920 --> 00:53:33,360
I said stop the car.

830
00:53:33,680 --> 00:53:35,320
Go back home.

831
00:53:40,640 --> 00:53:41,680
Honey.

832
00:53:44,640 --> 00:53:46,480
- Go back home.
- Why are you following me?

833
00:53:47,560 --> 00:53:49,040
I said go home.

834
00:53:52,280 --> 00:53:54,600
She’s just your neighbor.

835
00:53:54,800 --> 00:53:56,960
Why do you have to protect her this much?

836
00:53:57,760 --> 00:53:59,240
Ever since we met.

837
00:53:59,240 --> 00:54:01,440
you’ve never yelled at me even once.

838
00:54:02,160 --> 00:54:03,960
Is she really that important to you?

839
00:54:06,320 --> 00:54:07,600
What’s wrong with you?

840
00:54:07,640 --> 00:54:09,720
Why are you so upset today?

841
00:54:09,760 --> 00:54:11,280
Whatever’s wrong with me.

842
00:54:11,280 --> 00:54:12,760
you don’t need to care about me.

843
00:54:13,720 --> 00:54:15,400
I’m going to talk to her myself.

844
00:54:15,600 --> 00:54:17,560
- Go back home.
- I’m not going back.

845
00:54:17,600 --> 00:54:19,320
- I said go home.
- I said I’m not going.

846
00:54:24,280 --> 00:54:25,280
Go home.

847
00:54:26,680 --> 00:54:27,840
What’s wrong with you?

848
00:54:27,840 --> 00:54:29,480
Why are you being so ridiculous?

849
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:33,360
Ridiculous?

850
00:54:35,880 --> 00:54:37,880
Being jealous of my girlfriend is ridiculous?

851
00:54:43,680 --> 00:54:44,680
From now on.

852
00:54:44,760 --> 00:54:46,920
don’t let me see your face again.

853
00:54:46,960 --> 00:54:48,240
Go wherever you want.

854
00:54:48,560 --> 00:54:49,560
Go then.

855
00:54:54,240 --> 00:54:55,440
Si.

856
00:54:55,880 --> 00:54:57,040
Come home.

857
00:55:06,760 --> 00:55:08,000
Si.

858
00:55:12,320 --> 00:55:13,520
Si.

859
00:55:13,760 --> 00:55:15,680
Please open the door for me.

860
00:55:20,080 --> 00:55:21,320
Si.

861
00:55:23,040 --> 00:55:24,080
Si.

862
00:55:24,560 --> 00:55:26,240
I’m sorry.

863
00:55:27,120 --> 00:55:29,480
I won’t raise my voice at you again.

864
00:55:30,320 --> 00:55:32,360
Please come out and talk to me.

865
00:55:35,440 --> 00:55:37,440
Go wherever you want, I’m going to sleep.

866
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:44,680
Put Jon the chicken in the car too.

867
00:56:50,160 --> 00:56:52,880
Si, what are you doing?

868
00:57:33,560 --> 00:57:36,120
It’s way cooler than Suphan Buri, right? Right?

869
00:57:36,120 --> 00:57:37,880
Stay strong, P’Klao.

870
00:57:38,040 --> 00:57:40,360
Don’t go soft on her yet. Stay strong first.

871
00:57:41,640 --> 00:57:42,720
Chickies.

872
00:57:44,480 --> 00:57:45,600
Honey.

873
00:57:45,640 --> 00:57:47,400
Uh, I’m here. Did the chickens leave yet?

874
00:57:47,400 --> 00:57:50,280
Uh, can I leave them here for a few days?

875
00:57:50,320 --> 00:57:51,400
A few days?

876
00:57:51,440 --> 00:57:52,440
P’Klao.

877
00:57:53,760 --> 00:57:55,760
When is she coming to pick you guys up?

878
00:57:57,280 --> 00:57:59,240
P’Klao.

879
00:57:59,240 --> 00:58:00,280
P’Klao.

880
00:58:00,640 --> 00:58:02,840
How could you leave me like this?

881
00:58:02,840 --> 00:58:04,800
Honey, I’m sorry.

882
00:58:04,800 --> 00:58:06,200
But I already changed myself.

883
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:07,880
(Dad's trying to find a good camera angle.)

884
00:58:07,920 --> 00:58:09,480
(Si, which side of the camera are you going to?)

885
00:58:11,000 --> 00:58:12,000
Okay, okay.

886
00:58:12,080 --> 00:58:13,080
Okay.

887
00:58:14,800 --> 00:58:15,800
The car won't move.

888
00:58:17,480 --> 00:58:18,480
Is it broken?

889
00:58:18,600 --> 00:58:20,600
-Your foot's still on the brake. How's it supposed to move?
-Oh right.

890
00:58:21,240 --> 00:58:22,280
(Officially flustered.)

891
00:58:24,800 --> 00:58:25,960
Hey, get me mango sticky rice too.

892
00:58:25,960 --> 00:58:28,080
(Soft Power.)

893
00:58:30,000 --> 00:58:31,120
("Running after love.")

894
00:58:33,160 --> 00:58:34,240
(Always staying close to take care of her.)
